# =============================================================================
# deno-mcp-template — environment variables
# =============================================================================
# Copy to `.env` and uncomment or set values. `deno task start` / `deno task dev`
# load this file via `--env-file=.env`.
#
# Naming: all server options use the `MCP_` prefix (parsed in `src/app/cli.ts`).
# CLI flags override environment variables. For collection-style options, use
# comma-separated values on one line (see README → Configuration).
#
# Documentation: README.md sections **HTTP security**, **Configuration**,
# **Production Checklist**, and **Runtime permissions**.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Transports
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Disable HTTP (STDIO-only). Conflicts with MCP_NO_STDIO.
# MCP_NO_HTTP=false

# Disable STDIO (HTTP-only). Conflicts with MCP_NO_HTTP.
# MCP_NO_STDIO=false

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HTTP listener
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bind address. Default is loopback-friendly local access.
# Listening on 0.0.0.0 or :: requires MCP_DNS_REBINDING=true and non-empty
# MCP_ALLOWED_HOSTS (validated at startup). See README → HTTP security.
# MCP_HOSTNAME=localhost

# MCP_PORT=3001

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TLS (HTTPS)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Both must be set together: PEM certificate and private key paths.
# MCP_TLS_CERT=
# MCP_TLS_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Custom HTTP headers (optional)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Comma-separated "Name:value" pairs, applied to responses. Example:
# MCP_HEADERS=x-api-key:demo,cache-control:no-store

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Streamable HTTP response mode
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# true = JSON-only responses (no SSE). false = default streaming behavior.
# MCP_JSON_RESPONSE=false

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DNS rebinding protection, CORS, and MCP transport Origin/Host checks
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When true, enables transport-level checks; you should set allowed origins
# and hosts for your deployment. Wildcard "*" is not allowed in origins—list
# each origin explicitly (README → HTTP security).
#
# With MCP_DNS_REBINDING=true, CLI requires --origin and --host; in .env set
# both MCP_ALLOWED_ORIGINS and MCP_ALLOWED_HOSTS (comma-separated).
# MCP_DNS_REBINDING=false

# Allowed `Origin` values (CORS + rebinding). Example for MCP Inspector + local UI:
# MCP_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:6274,http://localhost:3001

# Allowed `Host` header hostnames (rebinding). Example:
# MCP_ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1,app.example.com

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# HTTP security (shared secret for /mcp)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When set, POST/GET/DELETE `/mcp` require either:
#   Authorization: Bearer <token>   OR   x-api-key: <token>
# Prefer this variable over `--http-bearer-token` (avoids process list exposure).
# MCP_HTTP_BEARER_TOKEN=

# If true, startup fails when no bearer token is configured (CI / production).
# MCP_REQUIRE_HTTP_AUTH=false

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Rate limiting
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# If true, rate limits use CF-Connecting-IP, then first hop of X-Forwarded-For,
# then X-Real-IP. Only safe behind a trusted reverse proxy (README → HTTP security).
# When false, those headers are ignored for rate limiting (spoofing protection).
# Requests with no socket IP and no session id share a stricter cap
# (RATE_LIMIT_UNKNOWN_CLIENT in src/shared/constants/http.ts).
# MCP_TRUST_PROXY=false

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Deno KV
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional path to a persistent KV database file (default: platform default).
# MCP_KV_PATH=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Experimental MCP tasks (TTL ceiling)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Upper bound (ms) for client-requested task TTL. Default 86400000 (24h).
# README → Configuration. Validated in src/shared/validation/config.ts.
# MCP_MAX_TASK_TTL_MS=86400000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Other Deno / tooling (not MCP_ — listed in README Configuration table)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required for the `execute-code` sandbox tool (`@deno/sandbox`).
# DENO_DEPLOY_TOKEN=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Example: minimal Inspector + watch (matches `deno task dev` pattern)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MCP_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:6274,http://localhost:3001

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# EXAMPLE TOOL: fetch-website-info tool (SSRF policy)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Default: HTTPS URLs only to public hosts; private/metadata ranges blocked.
# Set to 1/true/yes to allow http:// for local demos (README → HTTP security).
# MCP_DOMAIN_TOOL_ALLOW_HTTP=false
